the direction of the CEO, manage strategic business initiatives from development through successful execution, and in collaboration with senior leadership. Near-term priority initiatives include strategic planning and goal setting, and how to best share stories about Truss\u2019 work through marketing and PR channels. Communicate and assist leaders with decision-making, program management, and prioritization of assigned action items. Collaborate with stakeholders to improve existing processes and coordinate organizational procedures for optimized efficiency and productivity. Help to define new operational strategies, working with the CEO and others on special projects. Ensure projects that spin up are in service of company strategy and goals. Establish feedback loops with employees to understand their perspective, identify themes and deliver on communications strategies that address their needs. What we hope you\u2019ll bring 5+ years experience in an operational or management role, reporting to a principal. Comfort with ambiguity. Ability to execute on a directive that may not be clear, and respond thoughtfully and analytically. Ability to think strategically, and act tactically. A penchant for building and managing relationships. Ability to quickly zoom out and provide a useful perspective on day-to-day operations. Experience translating an idea or request into a clear proposal, with a persuasive rationale, and that\u2019s teed up for easy decision-making. A communications style that is candid, compassionate and concise and can adapt to the needs of the intended audience (employees, executives, external clients, etc.) Experience planning and leading strategic initiatives. A bias toward action. The salary range for this position is $143,000-$172,000 per year. We value inclusion and welcome diverse viewpoints. You must be eligible to work in the US. Unfortunately, we are unable to sponsor work visas at this time. We encourage all interested candidates to apply! If t